---
// src/pages/_site-updates/2026-06-25-arcade-demo-heat-cycle-tracking.astro
export const updateMeta = {
  date: '2026-06-25',
  title: 'Interactive Arcade demo embedded on heat-tracking pitch pages',
  tags: ['demo', 'conversion', 'heat-tracking', 'breeding-cycles'],
};
---
<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">June 25, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">
    Replaced the text-only "How BreederHQ handles it" pitch on three heat/cycle pages with a live interactive walkthrough of the real workflow.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-4 mb-2">What changed</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-1">
    <li>Embedded the "Track and Manage a Dog's Reproductive Cycle" Arcade demo as a new "See it in action" section on <a href="/workflows/heat-tracking" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/workflows/heat-tracking</a>, <a href="/heat-cycle-tracking" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/heat-cycle-tracking</a>, and <a href="/workflows/breeding-cycles" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/workflows/breeding-cycles</a>.</li>
    <li>Each embed sits immediately after the orange "How BreederHQ handles this" pitch section and before the "Who this is for" qualifier, so the pitch sets up the claim, the demo proves it, and the qualifier lets visitors self-select.</li>
    <li>Iframe is lazy-loaded and uses Arcade's standard responsive aspect-ratio wrapper. Deprecated <code>webkitallowfullscreen</code> / <code>mozallowfullscreen</code> attributes dropped — modern <code>allowfullscreen</code> covers all current browsers.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-4 mb-2">Why</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
    The three pitch pages already had a "How BreederHQ handles it" section, but it was prose only — readers had to take our word for it. A working interactive walkthrough turns the claim into proof on the page, without sending the visitor off to a video host or a separate demo flow.
  </p>
  <p class="text-gray-700">
    The two utility/editorial pages in the heat-cycle cluster (<a href="/tools/heat-cycle-calculator" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/tools/heat-cycle-calculator</a> and <a href="/dog-heat-cycle-calculator" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/dog-heat-cycle-calculator</a>) were intentionally left alone — their job is to convert on the calculator itself, and a product demo would compete with the primary CTA.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-4 mb-2">Next</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-1">
    <li>Watch engagement (scroll depth past the embed, demo open rate from Arcade's analytics) before expanding to other workflow pages.</li>
    <li>If the heat-cycle demo performs, follow with workflow-specific demos for the other top pitch pages (waitlists & placement, breeding plans, marketplace listing).</li>
  </ul>
</article>
